      <div class="column_item">
        <div class="blog_date">
          <img alt="Tuesday 24 February 2009" src="/images/headers/pf_small/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Tuesday 24 February 2009" />
        </div>
        <div class="blog_headline">
          <img alt="Wanted Voice-Over Talent " src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Wanted Voice-Over Talent " />
        </div>
        <div class="blog_text">
          <p>
            <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_txtText"><p><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">
<p style="margin-left: 36pt; text-align: center" align="left"><br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
UNIVERSAL PICTURES<span style="color: navy"> </span>DIGITAL PLATFORMS GROUP <st1:stockticker w:st="on">AND</st1:stockticker> WARNER BROS. INTERACTIVE ENTERTAINMENT ANNOUNCE VOICE-OVER TALENT FOR <st1:stockticker w:st="on">EPIC</st1:stockticker> ACTION VIDEOGAME<em> <a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">WANTED: WEAPONS OF FATE</a></em></p>
</span></strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt; text-align: center" align="left"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt; text-align: center" align="center"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">Wanted<em> Stars Common, Thomas Kretschmann and Terence Stamp Join Paz Vega in Lending their Voices to the Videogame Based on Universal Pictures&rsquo; Blockbuster Action-Thriller</em></span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">Burbank, Calif. &ndash; February 5, 2009 &ndash; Universal Pictures Digital Platforms Group and Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment today revealed that Grammy<sup>&reg;</sup> Award winning hip-hop artist and actor Common (<em>American Gangster</em>,<em> Smokin&rsquo; Aces</em>), noted actor Thomas Kretschmann (<em>King Kong</em>,<em> Transsiberian</em>), award-winning Spanish actress Paz Vega (<em>Spanglish</em>,<em> The Spirit</em>) and Oscar<sup>&reg;</sup>-nominated film star Terence Stamp (<em>Superman II</em>,<em> Valkyrie</em>) will lend their vocal talents to the highly anticipated videogame<strong><em> <a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></em></strong>, based on Universal Pictures&rsquo; blockbuster action-thriller<em> Wanted</em>. </span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><strong><em><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'"><a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></span></em></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'"> is one of two self-funded games announced by Universal Pictures Digital Platforms Group this year and is being created in partnership with renowned developer <st1:stockticker w:st="on">GRIN</st1:stockticker>.&nbsp; The game will be published worldwide by Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment.</span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">In<strong><em> <a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></em>,</strong> Common voices the role of Brummel, a businessman and weapons dealer with ties to a secret society of assassins known as the Fraternity, while Paz Vega plays a seductive Spanish assassin named Ara&ntilde;a who protects one of the Fraternity&rsquo;s innermost secrets.&nbsp; Terence Stamp returns to his role from the film as Pekwarsky, a close friend of the Killer who has shrouded affiliations with the team of assassins.&nbsp; </span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">Other vocal talents in the game include performances from Thomas Kretschmann, who reprises his film role as Cross, a former member of the Fraternity who finds himself the target of those who were once his allies.&nbsp; Additionally, award-winning actor Peter Stormare (<em>Constantine</em>,<em> Nacho Libre</em>) lends his voice as The Immortal, the leader of the French Fraternity who will stop at nothing to follow the film&rsquo;s notable Code of Weavers.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
<strong><em><a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></em></strong> is an intense, third-person action-thriller that takes combat to a new level with iconic techniques and moves drawn directly from the film &mdash; such as &ldquo;Curving Bullets&rdquo; and &ldquo;Assassin Time&rdquo; &mdash; as well as an innovative, multi-layered cover mechanic.&nbsp; The storyline of the game picks up where the film leaves off, providing fans with a new stage to explore in hero Wesley&rsquo;s journey to becoming an unparalleled enforcer of justice.&nbsp; The game allows users to create another chapter in the epic fiction of the Fraternity. </span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><strong><em><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'"><a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></span></em></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'"> is inspired by the blockbuster feature film<em> Wanted</em>,&nbsp;which recently debuted on <st1:stockticker w:st="on">DVD</st1:stockticker> and Blu-ray Hi-Def from Universal Studios Home Entertainment.&nbsp; Starring James McAvoy, Morgan Freeman and Angelina Jolie as members of an elite team of assassins who live by an ancient, unbreakable code, the action-thriller is&nbsp;available in stores now.</span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 36pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial','sans-serif'">In development since early 2007,<strong><em> <a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">Wanted: Weapons of Fate</a></em></strong> will be available in March 2009 on the Xbox 360&reg; video game and entertainment system from Microsoft, PLAYSTATION&reg;3 Computer Entertainment System and PC.&nbsp; For more information on the video game and the film, please visit <a href="http://www.wantedvideogame.com/">www.wantedvideogame.com</a></span><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p></span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="blog_end">
          <img src="img/blog/blog_posted_by.png" width="28" height="15" />Posted by
          <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#112;&#114;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#64;&#103;&#114;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#115;&#101;">Gunnar</a>
          at
          <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblTime">08:59</span></div>
      </div>
